            <h2>How Do I Get Around Inside Terminal 4? </h2>
            <p>Terminal 4 is big but is also well laid out with four major concourses (A, B, C, and D). Each concourse has its own set of gates. You will find your gate number listed on your boarding pass and you can also check on the airport's many screens. The concourses are connected, and you can also enjoy a great walk along the Sky Harbor Fitness Trail, which links Concourses A and D, offering a nice way to stretch your legs. </p>
            <h2>What About Food, Shops, and Other Services? </h2>
            <p>Terminal 4 has tons of options to keep you busy and comfortable. In terms of food and drinks, you will find everything from quick snacks at Starbucks or Dunkin' to sit-down restaurants. There are also many local food places and well-known food chains offering coffee, sandwiches, and sit-down meals and bars. On the other hand, for a great shopping experience, you need a last-minute souvenir and a good book or even some fashion items, and T4 has a wide range of shops. There are many leading lounges available, and you can access them through your airline, credit card, or by purchasing a day pass. Here are the lounge options -</p>
            <p>American Airlines Admirals Club</p>
